LONDON. Alexis Sanchez says the ball is in Arsenal s court as his contract saga drags on.The Gunners are deseprate to tie the Chilean to a new deal. His present contract expires in 18 months and Arsenal want him to stay long-term.But no deal has been agreed between the player and the club. I m focused more on winning football matches &#8211; I m staying concentrated on that, he told Sky Sports when quizzed over his desire to sign a new deal. It really doesn t depend on me &#8211; if they want to show confidence in me. I m very happy at the club. I love all the staff. I m very grateful for everybody here. It depends on Arsenal. I enjoy the relationship with the fans. I want to achieve more for them. I want to win the Premier League and the Champions League. The Daily Star.